1
00:01:09,002 --> 00:01:10,595
Where you going?

2
00:01:12,338 --> 00:01:14,636
I asked you a question, cabron!

3
00:01:39,899 --> 00:01:41,196
Much obliged.

4
00:01:56,382 --> 00:01:59,317
Could you tell me
how to get to Los Portales?

5
00:03:38,117 --> 00:03:39,516
Howdy, Luis!

6
00:03:43,156 --> 00:03:44,954
Where are the others?

7
00:03:45,558 --> 00:03:46,650
Gone.

8
00:03:49,095 --> 00:03:50,460
Not Hector.

9
00:03:54,834 --> 00:03:57,132
- They're all dead.
- He's a liar!

10
00:03:59,138 --> 00:04:01,038
Who has done this thing?

11
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:02,769
Gringo.

12
00:04:04,010 --> 00:04:05,739
A blind one.

13
00:04:06,346 --> 00:04:09,907
He could not see,
but he could shoot, I swear!

14
00:04:10,950 --> 00:04:12,850
He had a baby with him.

15
00:04:13,786 --> 00:04:14,844
Yes!

16
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:20,556
This blind one who shot Hector.

17
00:04:21,361 --> 00:04:23,261
The one with the baby.

18
00:04:23,796 --> 00:04:25,787
How come he didn't kill you?

19
00:04:26,332 --> 00:04:29,233
Didn'tI tell you to guard the road, Luis?

20
00:04:29,669 --> 00:04:33,572
I have a feeling that maybe
you got tired of waiting.

21
00:04:35,608 --> 00:04:38,976
I, too, am tired of waiting.

22
00:04:39,078 --> 00:04:40,705
- That's right!
- Same here.

23
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:45,377
Roberto, take Coyote and Vato,
ride to San Pedro, find Hector.

24
00:04:46,419 --> 00:04:49,411
Papa, I think we should wait.
They'll come back soon.

25
00:04:49,522 --> 00:04:53,015
Kid's right. We got them blue bellies
holed up like a bunch of ticks.

26
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:55,484
That silver ain't going nowhere.

27
00:04:55,561 --> 00:04:57,529
They have to give it up.

28
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:00,459
Find your brother.

29
00:05:06,906 --> 00:05:09,375
Water. Help me. Water!

30
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:12,974
Give him some water.

31
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:15,345
Can't you see the man is thirsty?

32
00:05:15,581 --> 00:05:16,776
Water.

33
00:05:37,103 --> 00:05:40,539
Looks like the man needs a chaser.
What do you think?

34
00:05:43,209 --> 00:05:44,233
No.

35
00:05:45,645 --> 00:05:48,910
Maybe he needs something to eat.

36
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:56,221
No!

37
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:22,137
Don't want your soul here.
Get out of here!

38
00:07:22,308 --> 00:07:23,469
Go on!

39
00:07:26,746 --> 00:07:29,306
Just get out and stay out. Go on!

40
00:07:37,356 --> 00:07:39,688
- Good day.
- For some of us.

41
00:07:40,893 --> 00:07:44,022
- You heard of Los Portales?
- This is San Pedro.

42
00:07:45,565 --> 00:07:47,590
How did you get into town?

43
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:51,896
On the road.

44
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:54,037
On a horse.

45
00:07:57,677 --> 00:07:58,803
You're blind.

46
00:07:58,911 --> 00:08:03,246
You know, Father, I don't much like
the idea of drawing on a man of God.

47
00:08:04,417 --> 00:08:07,318
But I will if you don't drop that gun,
Mr. Holy Man.

48
00:08:11,691 --> 00:08:12,715
Slow.

49
00:08:19,365 --> 00:08:20,924
How do you know I'm a priest?

50
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:26,131
I hear them praying for you.

51
00:08:38,851 --> 00:08:40,012
Sarge!

52
00:08:42,688 --> 00:08:44,417
- Sarge!
- What?

53
00:08:46,626 --> 00:08:49,561
How the hell did he get into town
when we can't get out?

54
00:08:49,629 --> 00:08:51,996
How the hell do you think
he gotinto town?

55
00:08:52,465 --> 00:08:54,331
Who ya got posted out there?

56
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:55,696
Stiggs and Beecham.

57
00:08:56,269 --> 00:08:57,998
Stiggs and Beecham?

58
00:08:58,838 --> 00:09:00,203
That's how.

59
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:11,675
Damn.

60
00:09:33,639 --> 00:09:35,300
What's that noise?

61
00:09:36,609 --> 00:09:37,770
Noise?

62
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:44,780
Indians say it's the gods
doing a war dance. How about that?

63
00:09:46,185 --> 00:09:49,712
Sounds to me like the gods
got themselves some dynamite.

64
00:09:50,890 --> 00:09:53,791
- What can I do for you?
- Just get whiskey.

65
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:56,360
And a little milk...

66
00:09:56,896 --> 00:09:58,796
for this baby here.

67
00:10:03,970 --> 00:10:05,199
No milk!

68
00:10:07,773 --> 00:10:10,105
Well now, do you want a whiskey?

69
00:10:12,712 --> 00:10:14,373
No whiskey either.

70
00:10:15,481 --> 00:10:17,381
- You got cigars?
- Sorry.

71
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:20,150
What kind of town you got here?

72
00:10:20,386 --> 00:10:22,787
You got preachers who packiron.

73
00:10:22,989 --> 00:10:26,448
A man can't get himself a drink,
a little bit of smoke.

74
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:33,126
I got some mescal, private stock.

75
00:10:33,232 --> 00:10:34,825
That's gonna do.

76
00:10:37,403 --> 00:10:40,236
I'm looking for a town called Los Portales.

77
00:10:40,373 --> 00:10:41,738
Can't help.

78
00:11:24,617 --> 00:11:25,812
Hector.

79
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:27,778
Shit.

80
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:37,690
- These dead men belong to you?
- They just came with those horses.

81
00:11:37,930 --> 00:11:39,261
You're a funny man.

82
00:11:41,634 --> 00:11:42,795
What's your name?

83
00:11:42,968 --> 00:11:44,026
You the law?

84
00:11:44,336 --> 00:11:46,828
Closest thing they got to it
in this shit hole.

85
00:11:46,906 --> 00:11:48,237
You're cavalry?

86
00:11:48,307 --> 00:11:50,503
Hastings, Sergeant, U.S. Army.

87
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:52,901
The world is full of them.

88
00:11:53,345 --> 00:11:55,541
- What's that?
- Assholes.

89
00:11:58,451 --> 00:12:01,443
How did you get here?
I had sentries posted outside the canyon.

90
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:03,318
You should watch your hand.

91
00:12:08,994 --> 00:12:11,895
I'm looking for a town called Los Portales.

92
00:12:13,299 --> 00:12:14,824
You ever heard of that?

93
00:12:14,934 --> 00:12:16,424
Can't say I have.

94
00:12:16,502 --> 00:12:19,665
Then I'll just leave these boys with you.

95
00:12:20,706 --> 00:12:22,936
- Be on my way...
- You're not going any...

96
00:12:23,008 --> 00:12:24,442
- Wilcox!
- That's enough!

97
00:12:24,777 --> 00:12:25,676
Wilcox!

98
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:27,645
I said, "That's enough!”

99
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:38,654
You're looking for Los Portales?

100
00:12:39,191 --> 00:12:41,319
I can take you there if you help us.

101
00:12:41,393 --> 00:12:43,794
Hell, how do you know
he's not one of them?

102
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:45,888
See for yourself, Sergeant!

103
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:54,770
Do you have any idea who those men are?
Those men you killed?

104
00:12:55,908 --> 00:12:57,967
I can't say I do.

105
00:12:59,545 --> 00:13:01,741
Didn't really get a good look at them.

106
00:13:07,052 --> 00:13:08,850
That'll be four bits.

107
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:12,918
- There are three out there.
- You got 45 cents?

108
00:13:17,696 --> 00:13:21,860
About three weeks ago, Alacran's gang
chased Hastings and his men up here.

109
00:13:22,168 --> 00:13:25,297
There's only one road out of the canyon
and they've cut it off.

110
00:13:25,504 --> 00:13:28,030
There's no food, there's no medicine.

111
00:13:28,107 --> 00:13:30,804
There's no whiskey and there's no milk.

112
00:13:31,877 --> 00:13:34,346
- So what's he after?
- Silver.

113
00:13:35,381 --> 00:13:38,544
Apparently the soldiers
were headed for the mint.

114
00:13:38,617 --> 00:13:40,711
- Mister?
- Canaan.

115
00:13:41,821 --> 00:13:45,519
- Do you mind if I ask you a question?
- I been near blind since the war.

116
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:49,728
You've adapted quite well. That was
an impressive performance out there.

117
00:13:49,795 --> 00:13:51,661
Why thank you, Doctor.

118
00:13:52,598 --> 00:13:54,828
You don't much like doctors, do you?

119
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:57,301
The world's kind of full of them.

120
00:13:58,704 --> 00:14:02,607
I'm not a doctor, Mr. Canaan.
I was trained as an army nurse.

121
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:06,676
I grew tired of dressing wounds
and putting men back together.

122
00:14:08,914 --> 00:14:13,112
This was a peaceful town before
this business and I want peace again.

123
00:14:14,687 --> 00:14:16,348
Do you understand?

124
00:14:26,165 --> 00:14:27,826
Is this your baby?

125
00:14:29,068 --> 00:14:31,537
She just belongs to a woman
in Los Portales.

126
00:14:31,637 --> 00:14:34,163
I promised a man I'd take her there.

127
00:14:35,674 --> 00:14:38,473
I've just been having one hell of a time.

128
00:14:38,944 --> 00:14:41,345
- It's a very small town.
- Must be.

129
00:14:43,616 --> 00:14:45,277
You got kin there?

130
00:14:45,684 --> 00:14:47,015
A brother.

131
00:14:50,689 --> 00:14:52,714
- What's her name?
- Nothing.

132
00:14:53,626 --> 00:14:55,025
Just "baby."

133
00:14:56,362 --> 00:14:58,763
Poor man died just before he could tell me.

134
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:00,589
That's too bad.

135
00:15:01,166 --> 00:15:03,567
It was a shame I had to kill him.

136
00:15:23,389 --> 00:15:24,788
They got Stiggs!

137
00:15:25,024 --> 00:15:27,550
Man your posts! Close up that window!

138
00:15:27,693 --> 00:15:29,718
Damn it, men! Look lively!

139
00:15:29,962 --> 00:15:32,363
- He got Stiggs!
- Son of a bitch!

140
00:15:39,838 --> 00:15:42,637
- Damn, he got Beecham.
- I see that.

141
00:15:43,742 --> 00:15:48,179
You get yourself a clean chance at the one
with the shotgun, you take it.

142
00:16:01,493 --> 00:16:04,292
- What the hell you want?
- You know what we want.

143
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:05,825
In there.

144
00:16:05,931 --> 00:16:07,194
Forget it.

145
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:10,933
Tell Alacran that's property
of the U.S. government.

146
00:16:13,105 --> 00:16:17,008
You tell Alacran we got a full company
of cavalry on their way.

147
00:16:17,343 --> 00:16:20,040
- 100 guns, at least!
- 100 guns, at least?

148
00:16:20,679 --> 00:16:22,704
Good, who's bringing them?

149
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:25,247
Let's see.

150
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,451
It's Moody?

151
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:33,091
Walker? I don't think him.

152
00:16:34,727 --> 00:16:38,163
Gent? O'Riley, Pierce.
This is a long list, Sergeant.

153
00:16:38,230 --> 00:16:41,996
You want I should read them all?
Okay. Bennet, Calhoun...

154
00:16:42,234 --> 00:16:44,566
You shut your mouth, boy!

155
00:16:45,971 --> 00:16:47,962
They all hang from trees!

156
00:16:48,741 --> 00:16:52,700
Alacran, he nails them up for the ants,
crows and coyotes.

157
00:16:55,981 --> 00:16:58,382
Itis time to stop playing games.

158
00:16:59,985 --> 00:17:03,148
Haven't these people suffered enough
for you and your government?

159
00:17:03,222 --> 00:17:06,283
Aren't they hungry? Nothing comes in.

160
00:17:06,792 --> 00:17:07,792
Shit.

161
00:17:08,127 --> 00:17:09,993
The road is Alacran's.

162
00:17:11,463 --> 00:17:13,864
The road to San Pedro is the road to hell.

163
00:17:18,404 --> 00:17:19,404
Roberto!

164
00:17:23,275 --> 00:17:26,006
Get ready. My order, boys.

165
00:17:40,692 --> 00:17:41,716
Hector?

166
00:17:45,497 --> 00:17:48,990
Who did this? He died so you will die!

167
00:17:53,872 --> 00:17:55,271
Give him up!

168
00:17:57,876 --> 00:18:00,208
We start killing you one by one.

169
00:18:01,380 --> 00:18:03,371
This is your last chance.

170
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:06,043
You called me out?

171
00:18:25,871 --> 00:18:27,839
Drop 'em or I kill him.

172
00:18:28,140 --> 00:18:31,132
Wait! Hold your fire!
He's got one of my men!

173
00:18:31,743 --> 00:18:33,254
Drop them.

174
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:33,301
Drop them.

175
00:18:33,412 --> 00:18:36,006
Please God, I won't chase whores,
I'll quit gambling.

176
00:18:36,181 --> 00:18:38,445
I'll quit drinking whiskey, I swear!

177
00:18:40,586 --> 00:18:42,645
I'll be good, I swear I will...

178
00:18:48,026 --> 00:18:49,118
Fire!

179
00:18:58,170 --> 00:19:00,298
Got you, you son of a bitch!

180
00:19:02,875 --> 00:19:03,875
Shit.

181
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:06,703
Get him inside. Hurry up! Move it!

182
00:19:51,723 --> 00:19:53,350
Get back in line!

183
00:19:55,260 --> 00:19:58,662
I said, "Get back in line!"

184
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:20,348
I see we're awake!

185
00:20:20,419 --> 00:20:22,615
Where the hell are my glasses?

186
00:20:22,688 --> 00:20:25,316
- Put them on...
- Just get the glasses!

187
00:20:37,736 --> 00:20:39,261
Where's that baby?

188
00:20:39,338 --> 00:20:42,706
Lucille, she's fine.
She's asleep in my office.

189
00:20:42,941 --> 00:20:44,306
What do you call her?

190
00:20:44,409 --> 00:20:48,312
Lucille. Thought she should have a name.
A child deserves a name.

191
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:51,042
I don't like it.
It sounds like a whore's name.

192
00:20:51,316 --> 00:20:55,184
- What do you suggest?
- I suggest you mind your own... Christ!

193
00:20:55,821 --> 00:20:58,347
What's the matter,
afraid you may grow attached?

194
00:20:58,490 --> 00:21:01,653
- I'm not afraid of a goddamn thing.
- No, I don't suppose you are.

195
00:21:01,727 --> 00:21:06,028
If I want to name her, I will. I won't name
her something as stupid as Lucille.

196
00:21:06,164 --> 00:21:07,563
She's my...

197
00:21:08,066 --> 00:21:09,659
She's your what?

198
00:21:10,002 --> 00:21:11,663
My responsibility.

199
00:21:11,837 --> 00:21:14,306
She's not a responsibility, she's a baby!

200
00:21:14,473 --> 00:21:15,804
She needs love.

201
00:21:15,874 --> 00:21:19,640
You can't love something that doesn't have
the simple dignity of a name!

202
00:21:19,811 --> 00:21:24,305
If you can't manage that, leave her with me
and I'll find someone who can.

203
00:21:31,490 --> 00:21:33,857
Have you ever been abandoned?

204
00:21:45,904 --> 00:21:47,531
When do we leave?

205
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:50,270
- What?
- For Los Portales.

206
00:21:50,409 --> 00:21:53,003
- When do we leave?
- You said you'd help us.

207
00:21:53,078 --> 00:21:54,671
I thought I did.

208
00:22:02,821 --> 00:22:03,913
Evening, ma'am.

209
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:06,424
Johnson, get the window.
Franklin, the door.

210
00:22:06,491 --> 00:22:07,959
I don't like this.

211
00:22:08,026 --> 00:22:09,084
You!

212
00:22:10,095 --> 00:22:11,392
I said alone.

213
00:22:11,863 --> 00:22:13,490
These are my men.

214
00:22:20,672 --> 00:22:22,003
Dismissed!

215
00:22:25,677 --> 00:22:27,975
- Stand guard outside.
- Yes, sir.

216
00:22:30,615 --> 00:22:32,913
You got a problem with my boys?

217
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:35,847
One took a shot at me yesterday,
that's a real problem.

218
00:22:35,921 --> 00:22:38,413
- Impossible.
- You had a rifle in the bell tower.

219
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:41,387
- All my men were accounted for.
- Please.

220
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:43,024
Sit down.

221
00:22:50,268 --> 00:22:51,429
Drink?

222
00:22:52,738 --> 00:22:55,105
Where the hell"d you get that?

223
00:22:55,340 --> 00:22:57,001
That's private stock.

224
00:23:17,129 --> 00:23:21,794
How'd that piece of shit, Alacran, get the
drop on a bunch of seasoned veterans?

225
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:23,332
You go to hell.

226
00:23:25,604 --> 00:23:28,232
How much silver you gotin your wagon?

227
00:23:28,974 --> 00:23:29,974
One ton.

228
00:23:30,142 --> 00:23:32,543
And what are you warriors
willing to part with?

229
00:23:32,611 --> 00:23:35,945
- What?
- If I ride out and get you the help you need.

230
00:23:36,381 --> 00:23:38,281
I told you he couldn't be trusted.

231
00:23:38,650 --> 00:23:42,644
He has a point, Sergeant.
I believe some reward would be in order.

232
00:23:42,721 --> 00:23:44,189
Thank you.

233
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:49,126
His reward, ma'am, would be in the honor
of serving the interests of his country.

234
00:23:51,029 --> 00:23:52,929
- You find that funny?
- My country?

235
00:23:53,031 --> 00:23:55,329
Your country,
the United States of America! I

236
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:58,062
Son, my country begins and ends
right here.

237
00:24:00,338 --> 00:24:04,571
Your country's going to have to cough up
10 percent just to buy me and my services.

238
00:24:04,676 --> 00:24:07,475
Ten percent, 200 pounds of silver,
you understand?

239
00:24:07,546 --> 00:24:09,605
And throw in a box of those cigars.

240
00:24:09,681 --> 00:24:12,446
I stole this one off a dead man
and I'm getting sick of it.

241
00:24:12,517 --> 00:24:15,111
Forget about that.
I have men that will go out...

242
00:24:15,187 --> 00:24:16,814
You got men and they're dead!

243
00:24:17,923 --> 00:24:21,621
You got your whole goddamn regiment
out there right now rotting on trees!

244
00:24:21,693 --> 00:24:23,320
You got dead men!

245
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:30,666
Now, you can take it...

246
00:24:32,571 --> 00:24:34,266
or you can leave it.

247
00:24:41,046 --> 00:24:42,445
A blind man.

248
00:24:44,182 --> 00:24:46,879
And how did you know this man is blind?

249
00:24:47,185 --> 00:24:49,586
He had a stick to find his way?

250
00:24:49,888 --> 00:24:50,912
No.

251
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:55,620
- A tin cup, perhaps, to beg for the coins?
- He did not have a tin cup.

252
00:24:56,228 --> 00:24:58,356
He was wearing dark glasses.

253
00:24:59,364 --> 00:25:03,198
Because a man wears dark glasses,
this tells you he's blind.

254
00:25:03,435 --> 00:25:05,767
You are a bigger fool than Luis.

255
00:25:06,404 --> 00:25:09,704
One man kills five of my best men.

256
00:25:10,742 --> 00:25:12,369
He killed my son.

257
00:25:16,147 --> 00:25:20,311
I taught him how to shoot.
I taught him how to ride.

258
00:25:21,586 --> 00:25:24,886
With these eyes, I saw him kill 23 men.

259
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:33,497
