333
00:32:40,258 --> 00:32:42,750
I'm just twisting your balls.

334
00:32:55,940 --> 00:32:57,237
But then...

335
00:32:58,209 --> 00:32:59,973
you can't see it.

336
00:33:00,411 --> 00:33:02,937
Place might as well look good, right?

337
00:33:05,016 --> 00:33:06,506
You're a wise man.

338
00:33:07,352 --> 00:33:09,844
No. I'm a bartender.

339
00:33:16,027 --> 00:33:18,121
You still riding out tonight?

340
00:33:18,396 --> 00:33:19,989
That's the plan.

341
00:33:23,534 --> 00:33:25,696
- You don't mind my saying...
- Spit it out.

342
00:33:25,770 --> 00:33:27,738
You look ragged 'round the edges.

343
00:33:27,905 --> 00:33:29,100
Really?

344
00:33:30,008 --> 00:33:31,772
I think I look fine.

345
00:33:32,910 --> 00:33:34,071
Ernie.

346
00:33:36,814 --> 00:33:41,251
Today, I think I look like a goddamn knight
in shining armor.

347
00:33:47,992 --> 00:33:49,357
Mr. Canaan.

348
00:33:55,933 --> 00:33:57,458
Take my bottle.

349
00:34:02,140 --> 00:34:05,185
That's right generous of you.

350
00:34:05,209 --> 00:34:06,369
That's right generous of you.

351
00:34:08,413 --> 00:34:10,973
Damn fool, needs it a lot more than I do.

352
00:34:11,049 --> 00:34:12,517
I heard that!

353
00:34:53,758 --> 00:34:54,953
Canaan!

354
00:34:57,762 --> 00:34:59,787
Are you crazy, trying to kill me?

355
00:34:59,864 --> 00:35:02,196
What the hell are you doing here?

356
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:04,694
What does it matter to you?

357
00:35:04,902 --> 00:35:07,735
- How'd you getin here?
- The door was open.

358
00:35:31,496 --> 00:35:33,157
Get off me, bitch!

359
00:35:37,001 --> 00:35:38,662
I'm gonna cut you!

360
00:35:47,478 --> 00:35:48,673
That gun's empty.

361
00:35:50,081 --> 00:35:51,708
That gun's empty.

362
00:35:53,918 --> 00:35:55,545
This gun is full.

363
00:36:21,479 --> 00:36:23,072
Now she's empty.

364
00:36:46,370 --> 00:36:47,462
Bang.

365
00:36:49,207 --> 00:36:50,606
You're late.

366
00:36:52,009 --> 00:36:53,499
Where is Bull?

367
00:36:53,844 --> 00:36:55,039
Dead.

368
00:36:56,013 --> 00:36:58,675
I performed the sacrament an hour ago.

369
00:37:01,085 --> 00:37:02,883
Bull was my best man.

370
00:37:04,255 --> 00:37:06,349
What else did you have to tell me?

371
00:37:06,424 --> 00:37:08,984
The soldiers made a bargain
with a blind man.

372
00:37:09,193 --> 00:37:11,787
He leaves tonight for reinforcements.

373
00:37:14,165 --> 00:37:16,725
We will be waiting for this blind man.

374
00:37:16,968 --> 00:37:18,197
Alacran!

375
00:37:18,869 --> 00:37:21,065
The soldiers make a mockery of my church.

376
00:37:21,172 --> 00:37:24,699
They spit on the floor.
They swear in front of the altar.

377
00:37:24,775 --> 00:37:26,004
Alacran.

378
00:37:26,444 --> 00:37:27,843
Soon, Padre.

379
00:37:28,579 --> 00:37:29,876
You must have faith.

380
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:16,852
Get back in line!

381
00:38:25,202 --> 00:38:28,467
I said, "Get back in line!"

382
00:38:35,112 --> 00:38:36,546
Mama!

383
00:38:49,927 --> 00:38:50,951
No!

384
00:39:37,675 --> 00:39:39,268
What time is it?

385
00:39:40,911 --> 00:39:42,003
It's past 8:00.

386
00:39:42,079 --> 00:39:43,638
Is it day or night?

387
00:39:43,714 --> 00:39:45,079
It's night.

388
00:39:48,119 --> 00:39:49,917
Where are my glasses?

389
00:39:52,056 --> 00:39:53,683
I have them here.

390
00:40:07,338 --> 00:40:08,703
Hold still.

391
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:39,870
You better get that kid some milk.

392
00:41:14,071 --> 00:41:15,505
Don't go.

393
00:41:24,215 --> 00:41:27,947
And have these sons of bitches
keep taking me a piece at a time?

394
00:41:28,219 --> 00:41:29,846
I don't think so.

395
00:41:32,923 --> 00:41:34,789
Besides, we got a deal.

396
00:41:41,398 --> 00:41:42,576
I don't have a brother.

397
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:42,964
I don't have a brother.

398
00:41:43,067 --> 00:41:44,159
What?

399
00:41:45,202 --> 00:41:47,694
I don't know where Los Portales is.

400
00:41:51,375 --> 00:41:53,036
I lied.

401
00:41:59,250 --> 00:42:01,150
It must be a small town.

402
00:42:09,693 --> 00:42:11,320
You'll stay then?

403
00:42:16,634 --> 00:42:18,295
I'm past that now.

404
00:43:10,287 --> 00:43:12,312
- Here you go, Sarge!
- Good.

405
00:43:15,826 --> 00:43:19,228
We passed the surveying party
about 30 miles due west.

406
00:43:19,330 --> 00:43:23,130
They got a cavalry escort with them.
It's enough men to pull us out of here.

407
00:43:23,200 --> 00:43:25,168
You just give them this.

408
00:43:26,737 --> 00:43:30,367
You say all your men were accounted for
during that shootout?

409
00:43:30,574 --> 00:43:31,598
Yeah, so?

410
00:43:31,675 --> 00:43:33,302
Nobody up in that bell tower?

411
00:43:34,278 --> 00:43:35,712
That's right.

412
00:43:35,779 --> 00:43:38,111
- What about that priest?
- Priest?

413
00:43:38,582 --> 00:43:40,983
Will he know I'm leaving tonight?

414
00:43:41,285 --> 00:43:43,151
Shit, everybody knows.

415
00:43:44,388 --> 00:43:46,015
I wager they do.

416
00:43:52,496 --> 00:43:54,521
You gonna wish me luck?

417
00:43:54,898 --> 00:43:57,128
Why don't you just go to hell.

418
00:43:57,234 --> 00:43:58,429
That'll do.

419
00:44:17,554 --> 00:44:19,750
Quit standing around, damn it!

420
00:44:20,057 --> 00:44:21,684
Get back to work.

421
00:44:51,455 --> 00:44:52,945
Here he comes.

422
00:44:57,428 --> 00:44:58,486
Now!

423
00:45:18,716 --> 00:45:20,548
Burn in hell, blind man!

424
00:46:27,384 --> 00:46:28,476
Halt.

425
00:46:29,787 --> 00:46:31,312
I said, "Halt!"

426
00:46:48,972 --> 00:46:50,940
Prisoner coming through.

427
00:46:52,075 --> 00:46:53,600
Watch yourself.

428
00:47:06,757 --> 00:47:09,089
- What is your name, sir?
- Canaan.

429
00:47:09,893 --> 00:47:12,362
Are you aware of this letter's contents?

430
00:47:12,462 --> 00:47:15,830
- He's blind, sir.
- That's painfully obvious, Private.

431
00:47:17,434 --> 00:47:18,526
Well?

432
00:47:19,937 --> 00:47:22,565
I'm asking you a direct question, citizen!

433
00:47:22,739 --> 00:47:25,037
I am only to speak
to the officer in command.

434
00:47:25,108 --> 00:47:26,769
I am.

435
00:47:27,811 --> 00:47:29,301
Bully for you.

436
00:47:29,413 --> 00:47:32,405
It says here, and I quote,
"This man who brung...

437
00:47:33,450 --> 00:47:37,853
"The man who brought this letter did so
only when we gave him 200 pounds silver.”

438
00:47:38,689 --> 00:47:40,157
Is this true?

439
00:47:40,324 --> 00:47:43,658
Am I to assume that you attempted
to extort 200 pounds of silver...

440
00:47:43,760 --> 00:47:46,354
We only got a 30-mile ride,
we best be on our way.

441
00:47:46,430 --> 00:47:49,764
I don't believe we will be requiring
your assistance, citizen.

442
00:47:51,068 --> 00:47:52,092
No?

443
00:47:55,405 --> 00:47:57,874
This citizen rode in Antino...

444
00:47:58,108 --> 00:48:02,102
and what this citizen has forgotten
about is more than you'll ever know.

445
00:48:02,179 --> 00:48:03,647
Chain him up!

446
00:48:04,081 --> 00:48:05,480
Stand still!

447
00:48:05,582 --> 00:48:09,177
If any harm comes to the people of that
town, I'm gonna hunt you down.

448
00:48:09,386 --> 00:48:12,515
I'm gonna kill every breathing thing
you ever loved.

449
00:48:12,756 --> 00:48:13,917
Is that clear?

450
00:48:14,324 --> 00:48:15,416
Soldier?

451
00:48:15,492 --> 00:48:16,823
Take him away!

452
00:48:26,069 --> 00:48:28,265
Alacran wants to talk to you.

453
00:48:29,973 --> 00:48:32,772
I should kill you
for letting him get past you.

454
00:48:33,977 --> 00:48:35,877
But I have a feeling...

455
00:48:36,546 --> 00:48:38,878
I'm going to need all my men.

456
00:48:39,483 --> 00:48:42,475
Even a piece of shit like you.

457
00:48:43,854 --> 00:48:45,913
- Cut off his ear.
- Left one.

458
00:48:46,390 --> 00:48:47,585
Connor!

459
00:48:48,792 --> 00:48:50,055
Not here!

460
00:48:56,533 --> 00:48:59,002
- Where are the rest of the men?
- On their way.

461
00:48:59,803 --> 00:49:00,895
Good.

462
00:49:01,772 --> 00:49:03,866
The cavalry is on its way.

463
00:49:04,374 --> 00:49:05,603
Oh, dear!

464
00:49:16,286 --> 00:49:18,618
You boys must be bored out here.

465
00:49:20,190 --> 00:49:22,386
They'll be hanging you when they get back.

466
00:49:22,492 --> 00:49:24,654
That should perk things up.

467
00:49:26,029 --> 00:49:28,157
What the hell are you doing?

468
00:49:28,832 --> 00:49:30,357
Catching flies.

469
00:49:30,767 --> 00:49:32,360
You caught that?

470
00:49:32,936 --> 00:49:34,335
Do it again.

471
00:49:47,918 --> 00:49:50,046
What in the hell?

472
00:49:51,555 --> 00:49:53,023
You're blind!

473
00:50:05,502 --> 00:50:07,027
Well now...

474
00:50:07,771 --> 00:50:10,001
that's painfully obvious.

475
00:50:11,608 --> 00:50:12,734
Private.

476
00:50:21,284 --> 00:50:22,945
Goddamned animals!

477
00:50:23,687 --> 00:50:27,248
No sign of life out there.
About a dozen more of these fellows.

478
00:50:27,357 --> 00:50:30,850
They must've known we were coming,
probably halfway to Mexico by now.

479
00:50:30,961 --> 00:50:32,190
Cowards!

480
00:50:32,329 --> 00:50:35,663
They've turned tail, men!
Let's give Hastings a taste of victory!

481
00:50:35,732 --> 00:50:37,222
Forward, march!

482
00:50:43,640 --> 00:50:46,041
Company, charge!

483
00:51:01,925 --> 00:51:03,984
Staring ain't gonna make them
come any sooner.

484
00:51:04,061 --> 00:51:05,153
What?

485
00:51:05,228 --> 00:51:07,663
What, reinforcements, that's what.

486
00:51:07,731 --> 00:51:11,361
Hell, if reinforcements was coming
they'd already be here.

487
00:51:11,635 --> 00:51:13,694
That's not what Sarge says.

488
00:51:13,770 --> 00:51:15,864
Sarge! He's the worst of the lot.

489
00:51:16,006 --> 00:51:17,872
You better watch your mouth!

490
00:51:17,941 --> 00:51:20,740
I've been doing this for 20 years.
I rode with Sherman.

491
00:51:20,811 --> 00:51:23,746
He was a bastard,
but at least he knew when to retreat.

492
00:51:23,847 --> 00:51:25,076
We got orders.

493
00:51:25,148 --> 00:51:26,343
Orders?

494
00:51:28,685 --> 00:51:29,880
Orders?

495
00:51:30,220 --> 00:51:33,713
Orders used to be a man fighting
for his land or saving another life...

496
00:51:33,790 --> 00:51:35,554
or some grand notion.

497
00:51:35,625 --> 00:51:38,117
I never thought it'd come down to this!

498
00:51:38,195 --> 00:51:40,823
Wagon full of metal
don't make no sense to me.

499
00:51:41,198 --> 00:51:42,461
That's enough!

500
00:51:42,532 --> 00:51:45,194
We could give it to 'em,
or they'll kill us for it.

501
00:51:45,268 --> 00:51:46,861
That's 'cause you're a coward.

502
00:51:46,937 --> 00:51:50,100
Coward. Better to be a coward
than to be a fool.

503
00:51:54,277 --> 00:51:57,303
Stand down. Stand down!
Everybody stand down!

504
00:51:57,447 --> 00:51:59,745
What the hell is going on here?

505
00:51:59,916 --> 00:52:02,180
- Ain't nothing going on here.
- Nothing, sir.

506
00:52:02,385 --> 00:52:05,548
Right. I will not tolerate fighting
in the ranks.

507
00:52:05,856 --> 00:52:08,826
We have a common enemy
and we have our orders.

508
00:52:08,892 --> 00:52:10,724
- Orders.
- That's right.

509
00:52:10,794 --> 00:52:14,992
We're to guard this shipment
and guarantee its passage with our lives.

510
00:52:15,065 --> 00:52:16,658
Am I understood?

511
00:52:17,400 --> 00:52:18,993
Am I understood?

512
00:52:19,236 --> 00:52:21,295
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

513
00:52:22,172 --> 00:52:23,264
Good.

514
00:52:26,009 --> 00:52:27,204
Listen!

515
00:52:27,978 --> 00:52:29,207
Shut up!

516
00:52:42,459 --> 00:52:44,359
What do you make of it, Sarge?

517
00:52:44,861 --> 00:52:45,885
No.

518
00:52:55,038 --> 00:52:56,563
Watch the road.

519
00:52:59,209 --> 00:53:01,507
Easy, boy. What happened?

520
00:53:02,846 --> 00:53:05,781
Too many... too many should...

521
00:53:07,050 --> 00:53:09,212
Excuse me, soldiers.

522
00:53:09,286 --> 00:53:10,286
Lie still.

523
00:53:10,754 --> 00:53:13,689
- Last chance...
- It's going to be all right.

524
00:53:13,890 --> 00:53:15,915
- Hold still.
- No chance...

525
00:53:16,359 --> 00:53:17,793
Step away.

526
00:53:18,028 --> 00:53:19,086
He needs help.

527
00:53:20,096 --> 00:53:21,291
He needs a priest.

528
00:53:23,233 --> 00:53:24,894
This man is dying!

529
00:53:25,168 --> 00:53:26,636
This man is dead.

530
00:53:27,771 --> 00:53:31,071
Look at him.
He's in the Lord's hands, woman.

531
00:53:31,708 --> 00:53:33,608
Now step away from him.

532
00:53:38,582 --> 00:53:40,983
You men, pray for this man's soul.

533
00:53:50,293 --> 00:53:52,261
What do you think, Sarge?

534
00:53:52,462 --> 00:53:53,930
It's a trick.

535
00:53:55,932 --> 00:53:58,162
That's Rafferty from the 5th.

536
00:53:58,301 --> 00:54:00,702
He's a good man. I trained with him.

537
00:54:00,770 --> 00:54:02,864
If it is Rafferty, he's gone brigand.

538
00:54:02,939 --> 00:54:06,170
No such thing as a good soldier
that deserts his company.

539
00:54:06,409 --> 00:54:08,377
No, sir, he's an honest...

540
00:54:12,048 --> 00:54:15,313
You men, look sharp!
Cavalry'll be here any minute.

541
00:54:16,319 --> 00:54:19,949
Quit your jabbering and get this corpse
away from my post.

542
00:54:21,491 --> 00:54:23,687
I said, "Quit your jabbering!"

543
00:54:24,995 --> 00:54:26,463
God damn you!

544
00:54:27,664 --> 00:54:29,462
God damn you to hell!

545
00:54:30,934 --> 00:54:32,698
Get him out of here.

546
00:56:05,295 --> 00:56:06,956
You killed my son.

547
00:56:07,831 --> 00:56:09,458
That's what they say.

548
00:56:09,833 --> 00:56:11,597
And what do you say?

549
00:56:12,602 --> 00:56:16,004
From your lips, I want to hear it.

550
00:56:16,272 --> 00:56:20,675
I say, there were three and they all needed
killing, and he was just one of them.

551
00:56:25,482 --> 00:56:26,506
Go!

552
00:56:32,789 --> 00:56:34,655
Tell me something, blind one.

553
00:56:35,158 --> 00:56:36,887
Can you smell fear?

554
00:56:38,261 --> 00:56:39,592
Sour milk.

555
00:56:40,196 --> 00:56:41,721
My son, Hector...

556
00:56:42,699 --> 00:56:44,690
did he smell of this sour milk?

557
00:56:45,001 --> 00:56:46,025
No.

558
00:56:47,604 --> 00:56:50,516
But I smell it on you when you ask.

559
00:56:50,540 --> 00:56:50,563
But I smell it on you when you ask.

560
00:56:51,141 --> 00:56:53,439
It's a pity you have no family.

561
00:56:54,978 --> 00:56:58,471
Because then I could take from you
what you have taken from me.

562
00:56:59,249 --> 00:57:02,184
But you are like a dog or a snake.

563
00:57:02,519 --> 00:57:05,648
All you have is the blood in your veins.

564
00:57:06,923 --> 00:57:09,449
And that I'm going to take from you.

565
00:57:11,361 --> 00:57:12,829
Drop by drop.

566
00:57:34,717 --> 00:57:36,583
While you are dying...

567
00:57:37,086 --> 00:57:39,612
think of the people of San Pedro.

568
00:57:40,490 --> 00:57:42,584
The ones who sheltered you.

569
00:57:43,526 --> 00:57:46,393
For this, they are going to suffer.

570
00:57:53,770 --> 00:57:56,262
Let's go! We have work, muchachos.

571
00:58:17,393 --> 00:58:19,191
What are we gonna do?

572
00:58:22,298 --> 00:58:23,561
Sergeant?

573
00:58:25,702 --> 00:58:28,535
Follow orders. Guard the shipment.

574
00:58:31,541 --> 00:58:33,305
We only got six men.

575
00:58:41,217 --> 00:58:43,311
We wait for reinforcements.

576
00:58:45,488 --> 00:58:48,253
Sergeant, there are no reinforcements.

577
00:58:49,092 --> 00:58:51,117
Everybody knows they're dead!

578
00:58:51,461 --> 00:58:53,122
I don't know that.

579
00:58:54,330 --> 00:58:58,767
But supposing they are, soldier.
What is it exactly that you suggest we do?

580
00:59:04,173 --> 00:59:06,870
I say, we surrender and hand it over.

581
00:59:20,189 --> 00:59:21,987
Any more suggestions?

582
00:59:30,133 --> 00:59:31,396
Good.

583
00:59:32,502 --> 00:59:34,027
Man your posts.

584
01:00:22,986 --> 01:00:25,114
Where the hell is that lime?

585
01:00:33,029 --> 01:00:36,932
Are you just going to stand there,
or are you going to help me?

586
01:02:54,771 --> 01:02:56,239
We surrender!

587
01:02:57,306 --> 01:03:00,867
For God, for country, for me, myself and I.

588
01:03:03,546 --> 01:03:04,775
Alacran!

589
01:03:06,415 --> 01:03:09,612
You promised to drive the heretics
from my church.

590
01:03:15,191 --> 01:03:17,592
First, I will eat the breakfast...

591
01:03:17,794 --> 01:03:21,355
drink some mescal,
then we will kill all the soldiers.

592
01:03:21,731 --> 01:03:25,497
After that, we will all go to the church...

593
01:03:25,635 --> 01:03:27,125
and celebrate the mass.

594
01:03:29,038 --> 01:03:30,938
I have waited long enough!

595
01:03:31,474 --> 01:03:33,909
I want them gone from my town now.

596
01:03:39,315 --> 01:03:40,407
Papal

597
01:03:42,285 --> 01:03:43,616
Your town?

598
01:03:48,724 --> 01:03:51,056
San Pedro belongs to me.

599
01:03:53,863 --> 01:03:58,300
Now, out of respect for God,
I will spare the church...

600
01:03:58,668 --> 01:04:00,636
but the town is going to burn.

601
01:04:00,703 --> 01:04:02,432
You're worse than the soldiers.

602
01:04:02,705 --> 01:04:04,173
That is true.

603
01:04:04,540 --> 01:04:07,032
But at least we are good Catholics.

604
01:04:10,213 --> 01:04:14,844
Now, fly away little blackbird.
Leave my men to the celebration.

605
01:06:03,159 --> 01:06:04,422
Dynamite?

606
01:06:06,829 --> 01:06:08,092
Medicine.

607
01:06:11,067 --> 01:06:12,330
Medicine.

608
01:06:13,769 --> 01:06:15,032
Dynamite!

609
01:06:15,338 --> 01:06:16,430
Boom.

610
01:06:20,042 --> 01:06:21,635
Boom!

611
01:06:30,086 --> 01:06:31,815
Everything's ready.

612
01:06:32,722 --> 01:06:35,657
That nurse they got there,
she's a fine piece of flesh.

613
01:06:37,760 --> 01:06:38,852
Good.

614
01:06:39,295 --> 01:06:42,128
You can bring her to me after the funeral.

615
01:06:43,065 --> 01:06:45,295
I will give her some medicine.

616
01:06:47,269 --> 01:06:48,498
Roberto.

617
01:06:51,741 --> 01:06:54,005
Get Remick, round up all the peones.

618
01:06:54,076 --> 01:06:55,976
Lock them in the cantina.

619
01:06:56,045 --> 01:06:58,639
I want you to guard them
until after I bury Hector.

620
01:06:59,015 --> 01:07:01,074
But I will miss the funeral!

621
01:07:01,917 --> 01:07:06,047
You have not proven yourself worthy
to pray for the soul of Hector.

622
01:07:07,656 --> 01:07:10,091
I could have killed the blind man!

623
01:08:05,114 --> 01:08:07,344
Who buried my brother?

624
01:08:08,751 --> 01:08:10,310
I'm not gonna ask again.

625
01:08:20,663 --> 01:08:21,824
Where is Hector?

626
01:08:21,897 --> 01:08:24,764
Buried up on the hill.

627
01:08:24,967 --> 01:08:26,332
Dig him up.

628
01:08:26,535 --> 01:08:29,698
Alacran wants to give my brother
a proper burial.

629
01:08:31,807 --> 01:08:34,105
He's been in the ground for three days.

630
01:08:34,543 --> 01:08:35,635
What?

631
01:08:37,413 --> 01:08:40,439
Shut up, and just do it!

632
01:08:40,749 --> 01:08:42,444
I'll dig him up.

633
01:08:45,354 --> 01:08:47,379
Do you want the silver?

634
01:08:47,957 --> 01:08:50,255
Should I take it for Hector?

635
01:08:52,061 --> 01:08:53,061
Sergeant!

636
01:08:58,167 --> 01:08:59,601
Itis time to give it up.

637
01:08:59,869 --> 01:09:01,860
You come on and take it!

638
01:09:01,971 --> 01:09:05,236
Do not force us
to spill the blood of the innocent!

639
01:09:05,674 --> 01:09:09,076
- Come out now and we will let you go.
- You go to hell!

640
01:09:11,180 --> 01:09:13,205
You are a very stupid man.

641
01:09:15,518 --> 01:09:18,510
But your men are stupid as well!

642
01:09:18,587 --> 01:09:21,579
My men are soldiers
in the United States cavalry.

643
01:09:21,924 --> 01:09:24,291
They are prepared to die for their country!

644
01:09:28,130 --> 01:09:30,155
With all due respect, sir.

645
01:09:30,666 --> 01:09:32,998
You're out of your fucking mind.

646
01:09:39,341 --> 01:09:40,740
Don't shoot!

647
01:09:41,043 --> 01:09:42,169
Wait!

648
01:09:42,311 --> 01:09:44,439
He's dead. We're coming out.

649
01:09:52,421 --> 01:09:54,048
We're coming out.

650
01:10:43,639 --> 01:10:45,437
Is that grave for me?

651
01:10:47,543 --> 01:10:50,638
I'm digging up Hector
for Alacran to bury again.

652
01:10:52,114 --> 01:10:54,276
- He's crazy!
- No.

653
01:10:56,285 --> 01:10:57,878
He's just upset.

654
01:10:58,654 --> 01:10:59,985
Now, me...

655
01:11:02,291 --> 01:11:03,781
I'm crazy.

656
01:11:30,552 --> 01:11:31,747
Remick.

657
01:11:32,588 --> 01:11:33,987
Stand guard.

658
01:11:48,771 --> 01:11:50,535
You'll come with me?

659
01:11:55,311 --> 01:11:56,540
Come on.

660
01:12:07,356 --> 01:12:10,053
- Put down the baby.
- It's okay.

661
01:12:10,326 --> 01:12:11,987
Put down the baby.

662
01:12:20,135 --> 01:12:21,603
Some nurse?

663
01:12:23,138 --> 01:12:25,266
You are very beautiful.

664
01:12:31,814 --> 01:12:35,546
My father says he's going to fuck you...

665
01:12:35,651 --> 01:12:38,177
after we bury my brother Hector.

666
01:12:38,287 --> 01:12:41,086
I think it is better that I fuck you now.

667
01:12:55,304 --> 01:12:57,568
Next time, I cut the baby.

668
01:12:58,140 --> 01:12:59,335
Okay?

669
01:13:01,977 --> 01:13:03,206
Okay.

670
01:13:09,685 --> 01:13:11,175
Nothing funny.

671
01:13:15,457 --> 01:13:16,618
Come on.

672
01:13:17,292 --> 01:13:18,817
Come on.

673
01:13:48,056 --> 01:13:49,854
Let go of that knife.

674
01:13:53,061 --> 01:13:54,859
Let go of that knife.

675
01:13:57,699 --> 01:13:59,997
How do you like your eggs, son?

676
01:14:03,806 --> 01:14:05,137
Scrambled?

677
01:14:30,532 --> 01:14:32,523
Alacran wanted an open casket.

678
01:14:33,469 --> 01:14:35,233
No, Father.

679
01:14:36,338 --> 01:14:37,338
Puffy.

680
01:14:39,808 --> 01:14:41,298
Will you say the mass?

681
01:14:41,510 --> 01:14:43,035
Who else would say mass?

682
01:14:43,212 --> 01:14:46,375
You shouldn't say the mass today, Father.
Not today.

683
01:14:46,448 --> 01:14:49,543
- Don't be a fool!
- Come to my shed, we'll talk about it.

684
01:14:49,618 --> 01:14:52,144
- After the funeral.
- No!

685
01:14:54,523 --> 01:14:55,718
Please.

686
01:14:57,759 --> 01:14:59,420
After the funeral!

687
01:15:18,614 --> 01:15:20,673
- He won't come!
- Who?

688
01:15:20,816 --> 01:15:22,306
Father Malone.

689
01:15:24,887 --> 01:15:27,083
We'll light a candle for him.

690
01:15:36,999 --> 01:15:39,127
Looks damn respectful, boss.

691
01:15:45,741 --> 01:15:47,402
Show some respect.

692
01:15:52,347 --> 01:15:55,442
- Have all the preparations been made?
- Yes, sir.

693
01:15:56,685 --> 01:16:00,679
- Bring the silver that belongs to Hector.
- I've got it right here.

694
01:16:02,524 --> 01:16:04,754
I want it to go in the coffin.

695
01:16:19,975 --> 01:16:21,500
What is it now?

696
01:16:23,211 --> 01:16:25,202
He's pulling up the wire.

697
01:16:26,682 --> 01:16:29,413
- They're gonna kill us!
- Damn it, man.

698
01:16:30,485 --> 01:16:32,044
- Pick that up.
- Sorry.

699
01:16:32,120 --> 01:16:33,485
Pick it up.

700
01:16:39,161 --> 01:16:41,220
I said I wanted this casket open.

701
01:16:53,141 --> 01:16:54,472
You devil!

702
01:16:57,179 --> 01:16:58,874
God damn you!

703
01:17:10,225 --> 01:17:11,225
Boom!

704
01:17:16,932 --> 01:17:17,956
No!

705
01:17:21,670 --> 01:17:22,670
The casket!

706
01:17:22,804 --> 01:17:23,896
Shit!

707
01:17:24,406 --> 01:17:26,807
Get that casket out of my church!

708
01:17:27,576 --> 01:17:29,340
Get out! Take that casket!

709
01:17:29,411 --> 01:17:31,607
They're trying to blow us up!

710
01:17:31,780 --> 01:17:32,872
Jesus Christ!

711
01:17:38,520 --> 01:17:39,544
No!

712
01:18:41,249 --> 01:18:42,580
Blind one!

713
01:18:44,086 --> 01:18:45,679
Can you hear me?

714
01:18:51,393 --> 01:18:53,054
I cannot hear you.

715
01:18:55,797 --> 01:18:57,458
But I can see you.

716
01:18:59,267 --> 01:19:00,860
The both of you.

717
01:19:07,876 --> 01:19:09,435
You are deaf now.

718
01:19:10,579 --> 01:19:11,808
As well as blind.

719
01:19:24,593 --> 01:19:27,028
No eyes, no ears.

720
01:19:27,629 --> 01:19:29,654
You are like a worm.

721
01:19:44,846 --> 01:19:46,837
This is for my men.

722
01:19:49,284 --> 01:19:51,218
And this is for Hector.

723
01:20:22,384 --> 01:20:24,409
I can't see you.

724
01:20:27,189 --> 01:20:29,385
And I can't hear you.

725
01:20:33,395 --> 01:20:34,954
You smell like shit.

726
01:20:46,875 --> 01:20:49,139
Take a bath, asshole.

727
01:21:04,392 --> 01:21:05,882
Find anything?

728
01:21:51,406 --> 01:21:54,376
Plenty more of that silver
laid out over half the town.

729
01:21:54,542 --> 01:21:56,670
You use it to build a new church.

730
01:21:56,745 --> 01:21:57,906
No priest?

731
01:21:57,979 --> 01:22:00,311
Hell, the world is full of them.

732
01:22:02,117 --> 01:22:03,516
Here she is!

733
01:22:06,521 --> 01:22:07,920
Here you go.

734
01:22:15,463 --> 01:22:18,660
You sure you don't have a brother
in Los Portales?

735
01:22:19,834 --> 01:22:23,828
I wish I knew where it was.
I've asked everyone, nobody does.

736
01:22:26,374 --> 01:22:29,571
- You sure you're gonna be all right?
- I'm gonna be fine.

737
01:22:30,378 --> 01:22:32,210
- No more ringing in the ears?
- What?

738
01:22:36,451 --> 01:22:37,475
No.

739
01:22:44,626 --> 01:22:46,219
No more ringing.

740
01:22:47,362 --> 01:22:48,852
Maybe he lied.

741
01:22:50,365 --> 01:22:52,129
That man you killed.

742
01:22:53,835 --> 01:22:56,463
Maybe Los Portales doesn't even exist.

743
01:22:58,473 --> 01:22:59,804
Maybe.

744
01:23:01,443 --> 01:23:03,138
But I made a promise.

745
01:23:05,647 --> 01:23:06,842
I know.

746
01:23:28,770 --> 01:23:30,295
What do you think of Nell?

747
01:23:30,872 --> 01:23:31,964
Nell?

748
01:23:32,640 --> 01:23:34,665
For this little baby here.

749
01:23:35,243 --> 01:23:36,711
Just for now.

750
01:23:39,714 --> 01:23:41,478
Nell was my mother's name.

751
01:23:43,551 --> 01:23:45,280
I think that would be fine.

